Fix pytest warning

Class name used for instantiating a flask app with testing config was 'TestApp'; however, py.test thinks anything beginning with 'Test...' contains tests that should be run. Renaming the class fixes the warning.

Update requirements.txt

No need for argparse, since it's part of stdlib in Python 2.7 and >= 3.3

Set minimum Flask version since test on version < 0.10 fail due to no `_compat` module.

Switch PyPI classifier tags from Python 3.3 to 3.4 & 3.5

3.3 may still work, but we no longer test it.

Switch Travis builds to using tox

Also switched to new container-based infrastructure. Dropped support for python 2.6
